Definition: marked by eagerness to resort to violence and bloodshed
Example: bloody-minded tyrants; bloodthirsty yells; went after the collaborators with a sanguinary fury that drenched the land with blood-G.W.Johnson
Synonyms: noun, attribute, bloodthirstiness, bloody-minded, sanguinary, marked, by, eagerness, to, resort, violence, and, bloodshed, tyrants, yells, went, after, the, collaborators, with, a, fury, that, drenched, land, blood, -G, W, Johnson
Category: adj.all
